This paper deals with the problem of fairly allocating goods among agents, which is a classic problem in game theory (cs.GT). The paper also uses mathematical optimization techniques to find an allocation that satisfies certain constraints, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The concept of maximin share is a well-known concept in decision theory and social choice theory, which are both closely related to machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves analyzing the complexity of the problem and finding algorithms to solve it, which is a common theme in computer science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with the allocation of goods among groups of agents, which is a topic in social informatics (cs.SI).
